extends layout

block content
  h1= title
  i This tool takes a XLSX file and transfers it into HubSpot properties.
  h3 #[a(href="/Importer Blank.xlsx") Blank Spreadsheet Template]
  p The following property types aren't currently suppported:
    ol
      li Calculation Equations
      li Boolean Checkboxes
      li Checkbox
      li Radio
      li Select (aka Drop Downs)
  p Other limitations:
    ol
      li Does not create custom objects.
      li #[strong You MUST use the Object Type's ID and not the object type's label on the spreadsheet! i.e. 0-1 instead of "Contacts"].
      i You can find it by going to your object in HubSpot then looking at the url. For example if you have the url https://app.hubspot.com/contacts/22311609/objects/2-7916663/views/all/list for object "Planets" then the  object type ID would be #[strong 2-7916663].
      li This applet will auto-generate a name for your property and group.
  p The API Requires the following scopes:
    ol
      li contacts
      li companies
      li custom objects
      li deals
      li e-commerce
      li products
      li properties
      li tickets
  p plus any other scopes you need wherein you will have to interact with the object.
  hr
  p If you have any questions or run into any weird errors, please get in touch with #[a(href="mailto:matt@aptitude8.com") Matt] or #[a(href="mailto:thomas@aptitude8.com") Thomas].
  form(action='/submit-sheet', method='POST',enctype="multipart/form-data")
    label
      | Spreadsheet in XLSX format:
      input(type='file' name='spreadsheet' accept=".xlsx" required)
    label
      | OAuth Token:
      input(type="password" name="token" required)
    input(type='submit', value='Submit')
